qas.question: Which song made a strong impression on Madonna?

answers.text: These Boots Are Made for Walkin

qas.question: Who sang the song these boots are made for walking?
Who grew up listening to David Bowie?
Name one of Madonna's major influence?

context: In 1985, <a3_0>Madonna<a3_0/> commented that the first song to ever make a strong impression on her was "<a0_0>These Boots Are Made for Walkin<a0_0/>'" by <a1_0>Nancy Sinatra;<a1_0/> she said it summed up her own "take-charge attitude". As a young woman, she attempted to broaden her taste in literature, art, and music, and during this time became interested in classical music. She noted that her favorite style was baroque, and loved Mozart and Chopin because she liked their "feminine quality". <a2_0>Madonna<a2_0/>'s major influences include <a4_0>Karen Carpenter<a4_0/>, The Supremes and Led Zeppelin, as well as dancers Martha Graham and Rudolf Nureyev. She also grew up listening to David Bowie, whose show was the first rock concert she ever attended.
